\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. O. arachnitiformis} Gren. & Philippe, {\i Mém. Soc. Émul. Doubs} ser. 3, {\b 4}: 399 (1859). Plant 15-40 cm. Basal leaves ovate-lanceolate, obtuse, the cauline bract-like. Spike 2- to 9-flowered, lax. Perianth-segments usually pink, rarely purplish-violet, whitish or pale greenish; lateral outer perianth-segments c. 10 mm, oblong-ovate, obtuse, the median outer oblong-elliptical or -lanceolate; inner perianth-segments 6-7 mm, oblong-, triangular- or linear-lanceolate, more intensely coloured than the outer, glabrous, papillose or densely hairy. Labellum 8-10 mm, suborbicular, obovate or somewhat square, subentire, rarely indistinctly 3-lobed, velutinous, with broadly conical, short, inconspicuous basal protuberances, sometimes with a narrow, yellow, glabrous marginal zone, usually with a small appendage; speculum annular or square, usually H-shaped, blue or dark purplish, with whitish or yellow margin. Connective acute. 2n = 36, 38.{\i  W. Mediterranean region.} Ga Hs It Sa Si.
